UID:cedar-season-0001@cedar.norCal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270301
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Golden Chanterelle Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Cantharellus californicus\nDifficulty: Moderat
 e\nHabitat: Oak woodland\, mixed forest\nSeason: Jan\, Feb\, Nov\, Dec\nPe
 ak: Mar\, Oct\nRegions: Marin\, East\, Peninsula\, Santacruz\n\nCalifornia
 's state mushroom and the world's largest chanterelle. Golden-yellow with 
 forking ridges. Rich apricot aroma when fresh.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Jack-o'-l
 antern mushroom (Omphalotus olivascens) is toxic. Grows in dense clusters 
 at tree base with true gills\, not ridges.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Peak after
  first heavy winter rains. Cut at base — never pull.\n\n— Cedar · Nor
 thern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
