DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270301
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Pacific Golden Chanterelle Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Cantharellus formosus\nDifficulty: Moderate\nH
 abitat: Douglas-fir and tanoak forest\nSeason: Jan\, Feb\, Nov\, Dec\nPeak
 : Mar\, Oct\nRegions: Marin\, Santacruz\n\nFound under Douglas-fir and tan
 oak in northern coastal forests. Similar excellent flavor to golden chante
 relle.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Jack-o'-lantern mushroom. Check for forking ridge
 s\, not true gills.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: More common at higher elevations 
 and Marin.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
