DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270401
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Yellowfoot Chanterelle Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Craterellus tubaeformis\nDifficulty: Easy\nHab
 itat: Mossy conifer duff\, Douglas-fir forest\nSeason: Jan\, Feb\, Mar\, D
 ec\nPeak: Apr\, Nov\nRegions: Marin\, Santacruz\n\nSmall funnel-shaped cha
 nterelle with hollow bright yellow stem. Grows in troops in wet mossy coni
 fer forest.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No serious lookalikes. Yellow hollow stem is
  distinctive.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Excellent dried — flavor intensifies.
  Look in very wet mossy spots.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foragin
 g App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
