UID:cedar-season-0010@cedar.norCal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270401
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Oyster Mushroom Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Pleurotus ostreatus\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat
 : Dead hardwood logs and stumps\nSeason: Jan\, Feb\, Mar\, Nov\, Dec\nPeak
 : Apr\, Oct\nRegions: Marin\, East\, Peninsula\, Santacruz\n\nFan-shaped c
 lusters on dead alder\, cottonwood\, and oak. Decurrent white gills\, mild
  savory flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Angel wings (Pleurocybella porrigens) 
 — small\, white\, on conifers only.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Harvest young b
 efore edges curl. Best sautéed in butter at high heat.\n\n— Cedar · No
 rthern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
