DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260401
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Candy Cap Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Lactarius rubidus\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabit
 at: Oak and tanoak woodland\nSeason: Jan\, Feb\, Mar\nPeak: Apr\, Dec\nReg
 ions: Marin\, East\, Santacruz\n\nSmall reddish-brown mushroom. Dried spec
 imens have a powerful maple syrup aroma used in desserts.\n\n⚠ Lookalike
 : Other small brown Lactarius species. Dried candy cap smells powerfully o
 f maple syrup — others do not.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Aroma only develops 
 when dried. Peak January–February.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California F
 oraging App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
