DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270301
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Black Trumpet Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Craterellus cornucopioides\nDifficulty: Modera
 te\nHabitat: Oak woodland\, often tanoak and live oak\nSeason: Jan\, Feb\,
  Dec\nPeak: Mar\, Nov\nRegions: Marin\, East\, Peninsula\n\nThin funnel-sh
 aped\, smoky gray to black. Extraordinarily earthy\, truffle-like flavor.\
 n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes. Thin black funnel shape is uniq
 ue.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Look DOWN — nearly invisible against dark soil.
  Outstanding dried.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
