DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260301
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260501
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 King Bolete / Porcini Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Boletus edulis\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:
  Under pine and Douglas-fir\nSeason: Mar\, Apr\, Nov\, Dec\nPeak: May\, Oc
 t\nRegions: Marin\, Santacruz\n\nThe prized king — brown cap\, white spo
 ngy pores\, meaty white flesh.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Satan's bolete (Rubrobole
 tus satanas) — red pores\, blue staining. Never eat bolete with red pore
 s.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Slice lengthwise to check for worms. Avoid any bol
 ete with red pores.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
