RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Matsutake Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Tricholoma murrillianum\nDifficulty: Hard/Expe
 rt\nHabitat: Tanoak and madrone forest\nSeason: Nov\, Dec\nPeak: Jan\, Oct
 \nRegions: Marin\, Santacruz\n\nHighly aromatic — spicy\, cinnamon-like 
 scent. Often buried in duff. Prized in Japanese cuisine.\n\n⚠ Lookalike:
  Smith's amanita (Amanita smithiana) — toxic. Check for spicy cinnamon s
 mell.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Distinctive spicy aroma is the key ID feature.\
 n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,HARD
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
