SUMMARY:🍄 Lion's Mane Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Hericium erinaceus\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:
  Dead or dying oak\, alder\, and maple\nSeason: Oct\, Nov\, Dec\nPeak: Jan
 \, Sep\nRegions: Marin\, East\, Santacruz\n\nSpectacular white cascade of 
 spines on dead hardwood. Meaty\, seafood-like flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No
  dangerous lookalikes. White cascading spines on hardwood are unmistakable
 .\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Harvest young and pure white before yellowing.\n\n
 — Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
