DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Prunus ilicifolia\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\nHa
 bitat: Chaparral\, oak woodland\nSeason: Aug\, Sep\, Oct\nPeak: Jul\, Nov\
 nRegions: Marin\, East\, Peninsula\n\nNative cherry with thin edible fruit
  flesh over large pit. Traditional Ohlone food.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Pit and 
 leaves are toxic (cyanogenic). Only the fruit flesh is edible — never cr
 ack the pit.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Very thin edible flesh — best processe
 d. Do NOT crack the pit.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:FRUITS,HARD
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
