DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌊 California Kombu Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Laminaria setchellii\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHa
 bitat: Intertidal rock pools\, exposed subtidal zone\nSeason: Jun\, Jul\nP
 eak: May\, Aug\nRegions: Sonoma\, Mendocino\n\nHarvested commercially alon
 g the Sonoma Coast since the 1990s by Strong Arm Farm. Thick leathery blad
 es used in broths and dashi. Highest natural glutamate content of any loca
 l seaweed — deep umami flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes
  — large flat brown kelp blades on rocks.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Harvest J
 une–July at low tide only. Cut blade leaving holdfast intact so it regro
 ws annually. Do not rinse off white powdery surface — it's glutamates.\n
 \n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:COASTAL,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
