DESCRIPTION:PEAK SEASON for California Kombu (Laminaria setchellii)\n\nBest
  harvest window of the year.\n\nFull season: Jun\, Jul\nPeak window: May\,
  Aug\n\nHabitat: Intertidal rock pools\, exposed subtidal zone\nRegions: S
 onoma\, Mendocino\n\nHarvest tip: Harvest June–July at low tide only. Cu
 t blade leaving holdfast intact so it regrows annually. Do not rinse off w
 hite powdery surface — it's glutamates.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Califor
 nia Foraging App
CATEGORIES:COASTAL,PEAK
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cedar-season-0260@cedar.norCal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌊 Wakame (Alaria) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Alaria marginata\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabita
 t: Rocky intertidal\, exposed to wave action\nSeason: May\, Jun\, Jul\nPea
 k: Apr\, Aug\nRegions: Sonoma\, Mendocino\, Marin\n\nRibbon-like brown sea
 weed related to Japanese wakame. Subtly sweet\, tender after blanching. Ex
 cellent in miso soup and seaweed salads.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lo
 okalikes — distinctive midrib running down center of blade.\n\n💡 Harv
 est tip: Harvest before July when blades become tattered. Leave the holdfa
 st and 4 inches of stipe to allow regrowth.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Calif
 ornia Foraging App
CATEGORIES:COASTAL,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
