DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌊 Bladderwrack Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Fucus distichus\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: Mi
 d-intertidal rocky shores\nSeason: May\, Jun\, Jul\, Aug\nPeak: Apr\, Sep\
 nRegions: Sonoma\, Mendocino\, Marin\, Peninsula\n\nOlive-green branching 
 seaweed with paired air bladders. Rich in iodine\, fucoidan\, and antioxid
 ants. Primarily medicinal — broth and tea use. Found from the Sonoma Coa
 st throughout the Bay Area.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — 
 distinctive branching pattern with air bladders.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Harv
 est only the tips. Excellent for stocks and medicinal teas. High iodine 
 — use in small amounts.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:COASTAL,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
