SUMMARY:🌊 Turkish Towel Seaweed Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Mastocarpus papillatus\nDifficulty: Moderate\n
 Habitat: Mid to low intertidal\, rocky coasts\nSeason: May\, Jun\, Jul\, A
 ug\nPeak: Apr\, Sep\nRegions: Sonoma\, Mendocino\, Marin\n\nThick dark red
  seaweed named for its rough textured surface. Used as a natural thickener
  (contains carrageenan). Excellent in broths and as a umami-adding ingredi
 ent.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — distinctive dark red\, 
 bumpy textured fronds.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Harvest small amounts. Rinse t
 horoughly. Simmer in water — releases carrageenan to thicken stocks natu
 rally.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:COASTAL,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
