RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌊 Feather Boa Kelp Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Egregia menziesii\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: 
 Rocky intertidal and subtidal zones\nSeason: Jun\, Jul\, Aug\, Sep\nPeak: 
 May\, Oct\nRegions: Sonoma\, Mendocino\, Marin\n\nSpectacular kelp reachin
 g 30 feet. Air bladders make distinctive snapping pickles. Found washed on
  beaches after winter swells — no diving needed.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No da
 ngerous lookalikes — long strap-like fronds with feathery side blades an
 d small air floats.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Collect fresh cast specimens from
  beach — no harvesting of live attached plants needed. The small air bal
 loons pickle beautifully.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:COASTAL,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
