RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌊 Nori (Porphyra) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Pyropia perforata\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabit
 at: High intertidal rock faces\nSeason: May\, Jun\, Jul\, Aug\nPeak: Apr\,
  Sep\nRegions: Mendocino\, Sonoma\, Marin\n\nThe original wild nori. Thin 
 purple-black sheets that dry into crispy snacks. Rich in protein\, B12\, a
 nd iron. Harvested commercially along the Mendocino and Sonoma coasts.\n\n
 ⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — thin translucent purple-black s
 heets on rocks.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Harvest June–July on low tides. Dry
  flat on screens in the sun. Can be eaten fresh\, dried\, or lightly toast
 ed. Don't harvest near outfalls.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Forag
 ing App
CATEGORIES:COASTAL,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
