DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌊 Dulse Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Palmaria mollis\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat
 : Low intertidal shaded rocky areas\nSeason: May\, Jun\, Jul\, Aug\nPeak: 
 Apr\, Sep\nRegions: Mendocino\, Sonoma\n\nFan-shaped red seaweed with a di
 stinctively smoky\, salty\, bacon-like flavor when pan-fried dried. More c
 ommon Mendocino north than Bay Area. Exceptionally nutritious.\n\n⚠ Look
 alike: No dangerous lookalikes — hand-shaped red fronds in sheltered low
 -tide areas.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Harvest small amounts leaving frond base
 . Dried dulse fried in a dry pan until crispy tastes remarkably like bacon
 .\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:COASTAL,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
