SUMMARY:🍇 Wood Strawberry Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Fragaria vesca\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: Ope
 n forest edges\, disturbed clearings\, roadsides\nSeason: May\, Jun\, Jul\
 nPeak: Apr\, Aug\nRegions: Mendocino\, Sonoma\, Marin\, Santacruz\, Foothi
 lls\n\nWild woodland strawberry intensely flavored and sweet — grows abu
 ndantly in Mendocino clearcuts and forest roads. Tiny fruit with extraordi
 nary flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — classic strawbe
 rry leaves and fruit.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Forest roads after logging acti
 vity are prime spots — clearings create the sun exposure they need. Pick
  only ripe red berries.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:BERRIES,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
