DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260601
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Cow Parsnip Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Heracleum maximum\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\nHa
 bitat: Moist coastal meadows\, stream banks\, redwood forest edges\nSeason
 : Mar\, Apr\, May\nPeak: Feb\, Jun\nRegions: Mendocino\, Sonoma\, Marin\n\
 nHuge native plant with edible young shoots and leaf stalks in very early 
 spring. The raw sap causes severe phototoxic burns on skin in sunlight. Tr
 aditional coastal food for Pomo and other tribes.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: DEADLY
  lookalike: Poison hemlock (Conium maculatum) and water hemlock (Cicuta do
 uglasii). Expert ID essential before ANY harvest.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: EXP
 ERT ID REQUIRED. Harvest only young tightly-coiled shoots before unfolding
 . Wear gloves and long sleeves — sap causes blistering. Peel before eati
 ng. Cook thoroughly.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,HARD
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
