SUMMARY:🌿 Redwood Sorrel Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Oxalis oregana\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: Den
 se redwood forest floor\nSeason: Mar\, Apr\, May\, Jun\nPeak: Feb\, Jul\nR
 egions: Mendocino\, Sonoma\, Marin\, Santacruz\n\nCarpet of clover-like le
 aves on the redwood forest floor. Bright lemony flavor from oxalic acid. T
 hrives under the deepest redwood shade.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Cape sorrel (Oxa
 lis pes-caprae) — also edible. Wood sorrel is shade-forest dwelling\, ca
 pe sorrel is open disturbed areas.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Abundant in Mendoc
 ino and Humboldt redwood forests. Contains oxalates — enjoy as garnish n
 ot as main green. Flowers also edible.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California
  Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
