SUMMARY:🍎 Wild Grape (Vitis californica) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Vitis californica\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: 
 Stream sides\, canyon riparian corridors\nSeason: Sep\, Oct\nPeak: Aug\, N
 ov\nRegions: Napa\, Sonoma\, Marin\, East\, Peninsula\, Lake\n\nNative Cal
 ifornia wild grape vines draped over streamside trees in Napa and Sonoma v
 alleys. Small tart purple grapes excellent for juice\, jelly\, and wine. Y
 oung tendrils and leaves edible in spring.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous 
 lookalikes — classic grape leaves\, tendrils\, and fruit.\n\n💡 Harves
 t tip: Mark vines in spring when leaves emerge. Return in September when g
 rapes are fully ripe. Grape leaves best picked small and tender.\n\n— Ce
 dar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:FRUITS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
