DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260401
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 California Mugwort Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Artemisia douglasiana\nDifficulty: Moderate\nH
 abitat: Stream banks\, disturbed areas\, roadsides\nSeason: Apr\, May\, Ju
 n\nPeak: Mar\, Jul\nRegions: Napa\, Sonoma\, Lake\, East\, Foothills\n\nAr
 omatic native plant with silvery white-backed leaves. Strong sage-like fla
 vor. Traditional Pomo and Miwok medicinal plant. Leaves used for flavoring
 \, stuffing\, and smudge. Young leaves edible in very small amounts.\n\n
 ⚠ Lookalike: Other Artemisia species — all aromatic. Sage-like smell a
 nd fuzzy white-backed leaves are distinctive.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Used as
  flavoring herb — not eaten in quantity. Young spring leaves best. Stron
 g flavor — use sparingly like rosemary. Do not use during pregnancy.\n\n
 — Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
