SUMMARY:🍎 Toyon (Christmas Berry) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Heteromeles arbutifolia\nDifficulty: Moderate\
 nHabitat: Chaparral\, oak woodland\, coastal scrub\nSeason: Jan\, Nov\, De
 c\nPeak: Feb\, Oct\nRegions: Napa\, Sonoma\, Marin\, East\, Peninsula\, Sa
 ntacruz\, Lake\, Foothills\n\nCalifornia holly — bright red winter berri
 es. Traditional Ohlone and Pomo food. Hollywood named for this plant growi
 ng there abundantly.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — iconic 
 red berry clusters on native shrub.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Berries astringen
 t raw — improve dramatically after frost or roasting/boiling. Traditiona
 l preparation: roast or boil before eating.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Calif
 ornia Foraging App
CATEGORIES:FRUITS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
