SUMMARY:🌾 Wild Mustard (Sinapis) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Sinapis arvensis\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: V
 ineyards\, roadsides\, disturbed fields\nSeason: Mar\, Apr\, May\nPeak: Fe
 b\, Jun\nRegions: Napa\, Sonoma\, Lake\, East\, Foothills\n\nThe mustard b
 lanketing Napa Valley vineyard floors in spring. Flowers\, young leaves\, 
 and seed pods all edible. Napa wine country is famous for its mustard bloo
 m.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — classic mustard smell con
 firms ID.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Young leaves before flowering are best — 
 blanch to reduce bitterness. Flowers excellent in salads. Seeds ground int
 o mustard sauce.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:INVASIVES,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
