SUMMARY:🌿 Tule (Bulrush) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Schoenoplectus acutus\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabit
 at: Clear Lake shoreline marshes\, freshwater margins\nSeason: Apr\, May\,
  Jun\nPeak: Mar\, Jul\nRegions: Lake\, East\, Napa\n\nThe iconic tule of C
 lear Lake\, historically central to Pomo culture. Young shoots edible raw 
 or cooked in spring — peel the outer sheath to reveal a tender white cor
 e. Pollen edible like cattail pollen. Roots starchy.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No 
 dangerous lookalikes at Clear Lake — cylindrical stems without leaves ar
 e distinctive.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Clear Lake marshes have abundant tule.
  Young spring shoots are the best eating — sweet and cucumber-like when 
 peeled. Harvest sustainably — tule habitat is critically important.\n\n
 — Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
