DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261201
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Wapato (Arrowhead) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Sagittaria latifolia\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHa
 bitat: Shallow freshwater lake margins\, Clear Lake edges\nSeason: Sep\, O
 ct\, Nov\nPeak: Aug\, Dec\nRegions: Lake\, East\n\nAquatic plant with edib
 le starchy corms (root tubers) harvested in late summer and fall. Tastes l
 ike a mild potato. Important traditional food of many California tribes in
 cluding Pomo at Clear Lake.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — 
 distinctive arrowhead-shaped leaves.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Wade in shallow 
 water in late summer — push roots loose with your feet and they float up
 . Boil or roast corms like potatoes.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California F
 oraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
