SUMMARY:🌰 Blue Oak Acorn Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Quercus douglasii\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabit
 at: Dry oak woodland\, interior valleys and foothills\nSeason: Oct\, Nov\n
 Peak: Sep\, Dec\nRegions: Lake\, Napa\, Foothills\, East\n\nBlue oak domin
 ates the dry interior foothills of Lake County\, Napa\, and the Sierra foo
 thills. Acorns are sweeter and lower in tannins than coast live oak — le
 ss leaching required.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes.\n\n💡 H
 arvest tip: Blue oak acorns are among the best tasting California acorns 
 — lower tannin means shorter leaching time. Often only 1–2 changes of 
 water needed.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:NUTS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
