RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌾 Peppergrass Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Lepidium nitidum\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: D
 ry disturbed areas\, trails\, roadsides\nSeason: Feb\, Mar\, Apr\, May\nPe
 ak: Jan\, Jun\nRegions: Lake\, Napa\, East\, Foothills\n\nCommon invasive 
 with intensely peppery seeds and edible young leaves. Tiny plant but extre
 mely flavorful seed pods. Related to watercress and garden cress.\n\n⚠ L
 ookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — peppery smell and flat round seed po
 ds are distinctive.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Seed pods ground or used whole ad
 d intense black-pepper-like heat to dishes. Young leaves edible raw. Very 
 common on dry trails in Lake and Napa counties.\n\n— Cedar · Northern C
 alifornia Foraging App
CATEGORIES:INVASIVES,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
