DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260301
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260501
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍎 Western Redbud (flowers) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Cercis occidentalis\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat
 : Dry foothill slopes\, canyon walls\, chaparral edges\nSeason: Mar\, Apr\
 nPeak: Feb\, May\nRegions: Foothills\, Lake\, Napa\n\nSpectacular native t
 ree covering Sierra foothill canyons in magenta in February-March. Flower 
 petals are edible — slightly sweet and sour. Young green seed pods edibl
 e cooked like snap beans. Traditional Miwok and Nisenan food.\n\n⚠ Looka
 like: No dangerous lookalikes — brilliant magenta flowers on bare branch
 es in early spring.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Eat the fresh flower petals raw a
 s a garnish or in salads. Young flat green pods in April–May are best co
 oked. Mark trees when blooming — return for pods.\n\n— Cedar · Northe
 rn California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:FRUITS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
