UID:cedar-season-0321@cedar.norCal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260801
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261101
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌰 Gray Pine Nuts Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Pinus sabiniana\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat
 : Dry rocky foothill slopes\, oak-pine woodland\nSeason: Aug\, Sep\, Oct\n
 Peak: Jul\, Nov\nRegions: Foothills\, Lake\, Napa\n\nGray pine (digger pin
 e) dominates the Sierra Nevada foothills. Large seeds in heavy cones — s
 ome of the largest edible pine nuts in the world. Traditional staple of fo
 othill tribes.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — distinctive g
 ray-green sparse-needled pine with massive cones.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Con
 es are very heavy (3–6 lbs) — approach carefully. Green cones harveste
 d in summer\, dried until scales open. Crack with a rock. Rich\, resinous 
 flavor distinct from Italian pine nuts.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Californi
 a Foraging App
CATEGORIES:NUTS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
