DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Yampah Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Perideridia kelloggii\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert
 \nHabitat: Open grassy slopes\, meadow edges\, foothill grasslands\nSeason
 : Jun\, Jul\, Aug\nPeak: May\, Sep\nRegions: Foothills\, Tahoe\, Donner\n\
 nSmall white-flowered carrot-family plant with sweet edible tuber roots. T
 raditional staple of Miwok\, Nisenan\, and Maidu people. Sweet\, carrot-li
 ke flavor raw or cooked. Often the most abundant traditional food plant in
  Sierra meadows.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: DEADLY lookalike: Poison hemlock (Coniu
 m maculatum) and water hemlock (Cicuta douglasii) look nearly identical. C
 arrot-family expert ID absolutely required.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: EXPERT ID
  REQUIRED — Do not harvest without confirmed ID from a specialist. Anise
 -like smell of crushed leaves and small clustered tubers are key features.
  Water hemlock is deadly and in same habitat.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Cal
 ifornia Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,HARD
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
