RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Miner's Lettuce (foothill) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Claytonia perfoliata\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabita
 t: Moist shaded stream banks\, foothill canyon bottoms\nSeason: Feb\, Mar\
 , Apr\nPeak: Jan\, May\nRegions: Foothills\, Tahoe\, Napa\, Lake\n\nAppear
 s in large colonies along foothill stream banks and shaded canyon floors. 
 Named by Gold Rush miners who ate it to prevent scurvy. Same species as Ba
 y Area miner's lettuce but often more abundant.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dange
 rous lookalikes — round lily-pad leaves with flower through center.\n\n
 💡 Harvest tip: Look along shaded creek banks in foothill canyons in Feb
 ruary–April. Entire plant edible raw. Best before flowering.\n\n— Ceda
 r · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
