UID:cedar-season-0330@cedar.norCal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260701
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261001
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍇 Sierra Gooseberry Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Ribes roezlii\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat: 
 Rocky slopes and ridges in mixed conifer forest\nSeason: Jul\, Aug\, Sep\n
 Peak: Jun\, Oct\nRegions: Foothills\, Tahoe\, Donner\n\nNative gooseberry 
 of the Sierra Nevada with reddish-purple spiny berries. Intensely tart and
  flavorful. Important bear food. Traditional food of Miwok and Maidu peopl
 es.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — spiny gooseberry shrub w
 ith hanging berries.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Wear gloves — shrub and someti
 mes berries have spines. Tart raw — excellent in preserves. Bears compet
 e — check higher elevation shrubs first.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Califo
 rnia Foraging App
CATEGORIES:BERRIES,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
