DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Mountain Misery (Chamaebatia) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Chamaebatia foliolosa\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert
 \nHabitat: Sierra Nevada mixed conifer forest\, often with ponderosa pine\
 nSeason: May\, Jun\nPeak: Apr\, Jul\nRegions: Foothills\, Tahoe\n\nAromati
 c sticky ground cover smelling of pine and resin. Young leaves and flowers
  used as a tea by Nisenan and Miwok peoples. Not widely known as edible.\n
 \n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes in its distinctive sticky aromati
 c habitat.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Niche use only — sticky leaves steeped a
 s aromatic tea. Very small amounts — not a food plant per se\, more of a
  traditional herbal beverage. Distinctive sweet-resinous aroma.\n\n— Ced
 ar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,HARD
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
