DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Mariposa Lily (bulb) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Calochortus venustus\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\
 nHabitat: Dry grassy slopes and open forest in the Sierra foothills\nSeaso
 n: May\, Jun\, Jul\nPeak: Apr\, Aug\nRegions: Foothills\, Tahoe\n\nBeautif
 ul California native with a small edible starchy bulb. Traditional food of
  Miwok and other Sierra peoples. Nutty\, mild flavor raw or cooked. DO NOT
  HARVEST from protected or sensitive areas.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous
  lookalikes but protected species — only harvest invasive-area populatio
 ns with permission.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: ONLY forage where population is a
 bundant and on private land with permission. Bulb is small — dig careful
 ly with a digging stick leaving soil undisturbed. Cook like a small potato
 .\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,HARD
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
