SUMMARY:🍇 Dwarf Bilberry Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Vaccinium caespitosum\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabit
 at: Subalpine meadow edges\, rocky ridges\, moist slopes above 7\,000 ft\n
 Season: Aug\, Sep\nPeak: Jul\, Oct\nRegions: Tahoe\, Donner\n\nLow-growing
  blueberry relative of high Sierra and Tahoe. Small deep blue-black berrie
 s with intense blueberry flavor. Found on rocky slopes and subalpine meado
 w edges.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes at elevation — only s
 mall blueberry-like shrub in this habitat.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Look on ro
 cky exposed ridges above 7\,000 ft elevation. Peak late July–August. Ber
 ries tiny but extremely flavorful — best eaten fresh trailside.\n\n— C
 edar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:BERRIES,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
