UID:cedar-season-0345@cedar.norCal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270101
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Suillus Mushroom Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Suillus pungens\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat
 : Under ponderosa and shore pine exclusively\nSeason: Oct\, Nov\, Dec\nPea
 k: Jan\, Sep\nRegions: Tahoe\, Donner\, Foothills\n\nSlimy-capped bolete f
 ound exclusively under pines at Tahoe and throughout the Sierra. Large mea
 ty caps with spongy pores. Cousin of porcini — good flavor when peeled a
 nd cooked.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Other Suillus species — all edible but vari
 able quality. Avoid any bolete with red pores or that stains blue.\n\n💡
  Harvest tip: Always peel the slimy upper skin before cooking — it's les
 s digestible. Never eat if flesh stains blue when cut. Sauté at high heat
  to cook off excess moisture.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
  App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
