DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Fir Tips (spruce tips) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Abies magnifica\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: Mi
 xed conifer and red fir forest\, 6\,000–9\,000 ft elevation\nSeason: May
 \, Jun\nPeak: Apr\, Jul\nRegions: Tahoe\, Donner\n\nBrilliant lime-green n
 ew growth tips of red fir in spring. Bright citrusy flavor from vitamin C.
  Used in syrups\, salt\, vinegar\, and tea. Popular among wild food chefs.
 \n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes among California firs.\n\n💡 
 Harvest tip: Harvest only the soft bright-green new growth tips — they s
 nap off cleanly. Available just 2–3 weeks in May–June. Make into simpl
 e syrup or infused salt.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
