DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Labrador Tea Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Rhododendron columbianum\nDifficulty: Moderate
 \nHabitat: Subalpine bogs\, wet meadow edges\, stream margins above 6\,000
  ft\nSeason: Jun\, Jul\, Aug\nPeak: May\, Sep\nRegions: Tahoe\, Donner\n\n
 Aromatic shrub of subalpine bogs and wet meadows. Dried leaves steeped as 
 a traditional tea used by indigenous people across the Sierra. Mild\, slig
 htly resinous\, pleasant flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Bog Labrador tea is dis
 tinctive — fuzzy orange-brown undersides on leaves. Do not confuse with 
 toxic Ledum species — use established ID guides.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Us
 e small amounts for tea — large amounts can cause headaches. Dried leave
 s preferred over fresh. Found at the margins of high-elevation wet meadows
 .\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
