DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261001
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍇 Western Serviceberry Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Amelanchier alnifolia\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabit
 at: Rocky stream banks\, open forest edges\, canyon walls\nSeason: Jul\, A
 ug\, Sep\nPeak: Jun\, Oct\nRegions: Donner\, Tahoe\, Foothills\n\nServiceb
 erry (also called Juneberry or Saskatoon) — one of the most important tr
 aditional foods in the Sierra Nevada. Sweet\, mild berries resembling blue
 berries. Eaten fresh\, dried into pemmican\, or made into jam.\n\n⚠ Look
 alike: No dangerous lookalikes — white-petaled spring flowers and bluebe
 rry-like summer berries.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: One of the most underrated w
 ild berries. Ripe berries are deep purple-blue and sweet. Found along rock
 y stream banks in Donner Pass and Truckee areas.\n\n— Cedar · Northern 
 California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:BERRIES,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
