RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Mountain Sorrel Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Oxyria digyna\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: Rock
 y alpine and subalpine slopes\, talus fields above 8\,000 ft\nSeason: Jul\
 , Aug\, Sep\nPeak: Jun\, Oct\nRegions: Donner\, Tahoe\n\nAlpine plant of r
 ocky high-elevation slopes. Kidney-shaped leaves with intensely sour lemon
 y flavor from oxalic acid. Traditional food of many Sierra tribes eaten ra
 w.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — kidney-shaped leaves with
  bright lemony taste at elevation.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: High in oxalates 
 — eat small amounts as a trail condiment\, not a main green. Excellent a
 dded to trailside water for flavor.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Fo
 raging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
