UID:cedar-season-0360@cedar.norCal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Sierra Nevada Porcini Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Boletus edulis\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:
  Under pine\, fir\, and spruce in mixed Sierra conifer forest\nSeason: Jun
 \, Jul\, Aug\, Oct\, Nov\nPeak: May\, Sep\, Dec\nRegions: Donner\, Tahoe\,
  Foothills\n\nKing bolete fruits in the Sierra Nevada in spring after snow
 melt (May–July under pines) and again in fall (September–October). Tah
 oe and Donner area are prime locations — one of the best mushroom region
 s in North America.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Satan's bolete (Rubroboletus satanas
 ) — red pores\, blue staining flesh. Never eat any bolete with red pores
 .\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Spring flush under melting snowbanks is the classic
  Sierra find. Slice lengthwise to check for worms before keeping.\n\n— C
 edar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS,MODERATE
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
