DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Stinging Nettle (Sierra) Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Urtica dioica\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat: Mois
 t stream banks\, disturbed mountain meadows\nSeason: May\, Jun\, Jul\nPeak
 : Apr\, Aug\nRegions: Donner\, Tahoe\, Foothills\, Mendocino\, Sonoma\n\nS
 tinging nettle grows abundantly along Sierra Nevada stream banks and in mo
 ist meadows. Spring emergence is a few weeks later than coastal population
 s at same calendar date.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — sti
 ng confirms identity immediately.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: Wear gloves. Harves
 t young tops only at 4–6 inches tall. Sting neutralized by blanching 1 m
 inute or cooking. Rich in iron and protein.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Calif
 ornia Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,EASY
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
