DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 White Fir Cambium Season
DESCRIPTION:Scientific name: Abies concolor\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\nHabit
 at: Mixed conifer forest throughout Sierra Nevada\nSeason: May\, Jun\nPeak
 : Apr\, Jul\nRegions: Donner\, Tahoe\, Foothills\n\nThe inner bark (cambiu
 m) of white fir is edible and was eaten by Maidu and Washoe peoples as a s
 pring food. Scraped from fallen or recently felled trees only. Starchy\, s
 lightly sweet\, piney flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes am
 ong California white firs.\n\n💡 Harvest tip: ONLY harvest from fallen o
 r dead trees — never damage living trees. Scrape inner bark layer (green
  side of bark). Cook or dry and grind into flour. A survival food\, not a 
 daily staple.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging App
CATEGORIES:GREENS,HARD
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
